        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-11 16:22:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nHello, sorry to be the \"bad\" guy but it was stated that master shouldn't have \"staging\" versions and this merge break the rule.\n\nIs there a strong reason for this merge?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "7f120bfe3ad3319ee608793504bcfda38907bbd7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 33,
          "name": "James Forsyth",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jf2512@att.com",
          "username": "jimmydot"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-11 16:27:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Hello, sorry to be the \"bad\" guy but it was stated that master shouldn't have \"staging\" versions and this merge break the rule.\n> \n> Is there a strong reason for this merge?\n\nAre we supposed to release a new docker for every change and update our aai/oom chart?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "dd19c7dd8e801088cb56fa814848ae8ec1dd6f20",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2319,
          "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
          "username": "sdesbure"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-11 16:36:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> \n> Are we supposed to release a new docker for every change and update our aai/oom chart?\n\nI'll let Mike answer that but that's what I understood. That's why we proposed with Morgan to build automatically AAI dockers at each review (https://jira.onap.org/browse/INT-1360) and when it works we could automate also the chart update (or at least automate a review).\n\nsee also https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/PTL+2019-09-09?preview=%2F68547510%2F68548642%2Fintegration_verif_chain_for_PTL.pdf for what we should do",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d01f00d874b5a87c41b47ca082faf07c4a2a0c56",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 29,
          "name": "Brian Freeman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bf1936@att.com",
          "username": "bdfreeman1421"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-11 16:38:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nRemember we decided to can the staging branch of oom and use a staging-image-override file at the end of elalto since folks were messing it up so much.\nwe can re-review with Mike since the staging ovrride file (its a -f yaml to helm deploy not a separate script) for a staging install",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "ec8dd32e88f0c3053046f150cccb0eb9dd19d590",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 33,
          "name": "James Forsyth",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jf2512@att.com",
          "username": "jimmydot"
        },
        "author_role": "CI_BOT",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-11 16:46:35.000000000",
        "message": "Abandoned\n\nThis is the wrong approach; integration-override file should specify -STAGING-latest versions, not in the official aai/oom master branch",
